<doc id="1189629" wikidata="Q1921766" url="?curid=1189629" title="Nashville-class ironclad">
<text>The &quot;Nashville&quot;-class ironclad was a class of three side-wheel casemate ironclads built for the Confederate States Navy during the American Civil War. Only the lead ship of the class, , was commissioned into Confederate States Navy service; two sister ships were broken up on the stocks before they were completed.

