A West of Scotland Branch was established by an inaugural meeting held on 23 November 1894, to be based in Glasgow. In 1905 authority was granted to enrol members from the whole of Scotland, but it was not until 1937 that the name was changed to &quot;Scottish Branch&quot;. In 1954 the Branch seceded from the BAA to form the Astronomical Society of Glasgow.
*West of Scotland Branch Presidents 
**Walter C. Bergius 1895–1897
**John Danskin 1897-1899
**Rev. Edward Bruce Kirk 1899-1901
